owl:Class.terms:description: A process is an entity that is identifiable only through the unfolding of time, has temporal parts, and unless otherwise specified/predicted, cannot be identified from any instant of time in which it exists.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: process

owl:Class.terms:description: An emotion is a process (experience) that arises internally or from an involuntary physiological response to a stimulus.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: emotion

owl:Class.terms:description: intent is a desire to realize a particular outcome.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: intent

owl:Class.terms:description: perception is the organization, identification, and interpretation of sensory information in order to fabricate a mental representation through the process of transduction, which sensors in the body transform signals from the environment into encoded neural signals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: perception

owl:Class.terms:description: anger is disgust directed toward an equal status individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anger

owl:Class.terms:description: Hate is a deep and emotional extreme dislike, directed against a certain object or class of objects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hate

owl:Class.terms:description: love is an emotion of a strong affection and personal attachment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: love

owl:Class.terms:description: chemical synthesis is synthesis of a chemical entity from physical precursors through one or more chemical interactions or reactions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical synthesis

owl:Class.terms:description: passive transport is the movement of a substance across a membrane and does not require chemical energy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: passive transport

owl:Class.terms:description: diffusion is motion of particles at temperatures above absolute zero.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diffusion

owl:Class.terms:description: movement is the process in which an object is spatially displaced.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: movement

owl:Class.terms:description: Brownian motion is the seemlingly random movement of particles suspended in a fluid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brownian motion

owl:Class.terms:description: osmosis is the movement of water molecules through a selectively-permeable membrane down a water potential gradient.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: osmosis

owl:Class.terms:description: passive movement is the process in which an object is spatially displaced without an expenditure of energy contained in molecular bonds.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: passive movement

owl:Class.terms:description: active movement is the process in which an object is spatially displaced using some chemical energy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: active movement

owl:Class.terms:description: transporting is a process in which one object physically moves another object from one location to another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: transporting

owl:Class.terms:description: membrane transport is the movement of molecules across a membrane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: membrane transport

owl:Class.terms:description: primary active transport, also called direct active transport, directly uses energy to transport molecules across a membrane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: secondary active transport or co-transport uses electrochemical potential difference created by pumping ions out of the cell to transport molecules across a membrane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: secondary active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: symport enabled secondary active transport is a secondary active transfort in which both ion and molecule are transported in the same direction simultaneously.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: symport enabled secondary active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: antiport enabled secondary active transport is a secondary active transfort in which both ion and molecule are transported in opposite directions simultaneously.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: antiport enabled secondary active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: The self-propelled movement of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: locomotion

owl:Class.terms:description: birthing is the process by which a biological organism is brought into existence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: birthing

owl:Class.terms:description: dying is a process in which a biological entity ceases to exist.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dying

owl:Class.terms:description: biological reproduction is the biological process by which one or more biological organisms are produced from their "parents".
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological reproduction

owl:Class.terms:description: creating is the process in which an entity comes into existence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: creating

owl:Class.terms:description: regulating is a process that modulates the attributes of an object or process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulating

owl:Class.terms:description: biosynthesis is the synthesis of an organic compound in a living organism, usually aided by enzymes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biosynthesis

owl:Class.terms:description: destroying is a process in which something is broken down and/or ceases to exist.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: destroying

owl:Class.terms:description: chemical destruction is destruction of a chemical entity to its chemical constituents through one ormore chemical interactions or reactions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical destruction

owl:Class.terms:description: interacting is a process characterized by the interaction between two or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: interacting

owl:Class.terms:description: data transformation is the process of applying an algorithmic procedure to some input data and producing some output data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: data transformation

owl:Class.terms:description: A parameterized data transformation is a data transformation whose behaviour may be modified by one or more parameters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: parameterized data transformation

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a process is a process that modulates the duration, frequency, spatial extent of a target process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of process

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of capability is the regulation of the ability of one party by another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of capability

owl:Class.terms:description: the regulation of the enzymatic activity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of catalytic capability

owl:Class.terms:description: information processing is a process that involves the generation or use of information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: information processing

owl:Class.terms:description: software execution is the process of executing software on a computing device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sofware execution

owl:Class.terms:description: evolving is a process that elicits change across successive generations in the inherited characteristics of biological populations.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: evolving

owl:Class.terms:description: planning is the agentive process of developing a plan that specifies a set of actions in order to meet a set of goals or objectives.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: planning

owl:Class.terms:description: learning is the agentive process of acquiring knowledge.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: learning

owl:Class.terms:description: comparing is the process of examining a set of objects and determining their equality or inequality based on one or more features.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: comparing

owl:Class.terms:description: reasoning is the agentive process of using knowledge to evaluate the truth value of a proposition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reasoning

owl:Class.terms:description: investigation is the process of carrying out a plan or procedure so as to discover facts or information about the object of study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation

owl:Class.terms:description: predicting is the process of formulating a proposition about a state of affairs which might be realized in the future.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: predicting

owl:Class.terms:description: affection is an emotion characterized with a feeling or type of love for another living thing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: affection

owl:Class.terms:description: angst is the intense feeling of apprehension, anxiety or inner turmoil.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: angst

owl:Class.terms:description: Annoyance is an unpleasant emtion that is characterized by a abnormal or excessive sensitivity to some external stimulus.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: annoyance

owl:Class.terms:description: anxiety is an emotion charactersized by intense feeling of fear and concern coupled with a physical response.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anxiety

owl:Class.terms:description: apathy is an emotion characterized by lack of interest, enthusiasm, or concern.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apathy

owl:Class.terms:description: arousal is an emotion characterized by state of reactive to stimuli. It involves the activation of the reticular activating system in the brain stem, the autonomic nervous system and the endocrine system, leading to increased heart rate and blood pressure and a condition of sensory alertness, mobility and readiness to respond.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: arousal

owl:Class.terms:description: awe is an emotion produced by that which is grand, sublime or powerful and is characterized by a combination of joy, fear and admiration/reverence/respect.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: awe

owl:Class.terms:description: boldness is the trait of being willing to undertake things that involve risk or danger.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boldness

owl:Class.terms:description: boredom is the emotion experience by those not interested in their surroundings or available activities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boredom

owl:Class.terms:description: contempt is disgust towards a lower status individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: contempt

owl:Class.terms:description: contentment is an emotion characterized by acknowledgement and satisfaction of the current state of affairs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: contentment

owl:Class.terms:description: curiosity is the strong desire to know or learn something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: curiosity

owl:Class.terms:description: depression is an unpleasant emotion linked to aversion to activity that can affect a person's thoughts, behavior, feelings and physical well-being. Depressed individuals may feel sad, anxious, empty, hopeless, worried, helpless, worthless, guilty, irritable, or restless.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: depression

owl:Class.terms:description: desire is a strong emotion of wanting to have something or wishing for something to happen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: desire

owl:Class.terms:description: despair is depression, hopelessness or lack of hope.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: despair

owl:Class.terms:description: disappointment is the feeling of dissatisfaction that follows the failure of expectations or hopes to manifest.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disappointment

owl:Class.terms:description: Disgust is a feeling of revulsion or profound disapproval aroused by something unpleasant or offensive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disgust

owl:Class.terms:description: dread is the instense negative emotion that induces fear and apprehension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dread

owl:Class.terms:description: ecstacy is an emotion characterized by a heightened state of consciousness with total involvement of a subject.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ecstasy

owl:Class.terms:description: A positive emotion is an emotion that feels good.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: positive emotion

owl:Class.terms:description: negative emotion is an emotion that does not feel good.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: negative emotion

owl:Class.terms:description: Embarrassment is the emotion of intense discomfort with oneself, experienced upon having a socially unacceptable act or condition witnessed by or revealed to other.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: embarassment

owl:Class.terms:description: envy is an emotion that occurs when a person lacks another's (perceived) superior quality, achievement or possession and wishes that the other lacked it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: envy

owl:Class.terms:description: euphoria is an emotion characterized by intense feelings of well-being, elation, happiness, ecstasy, excitement, and joy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: euphoria

owl:Class.terms:description: excitement is a positive emotion of feeling great enthusiasm and eagerness.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: excitement

owl:Class.terms:description: Fear is a negative emotion induced by a perceived threat that induces one to hide or move quickly away from the location of the perceived threat.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: fear

owl:Class.terms:description: Frustration is an emotion that arises from the perceived resistance to the fulfillment of individual will.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: frustration

owl:Class.terms:description: Gratitude, thankfulness, gratefulness, or appreciation is a feeling, emotion or attitude in acknowledgment of a benefit that one has received or will receive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gratitude

owl:Class.terms:description: happiness is an emotion characterized by positive or pleasant emotions ranging from contentment to intense joy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: happiness

owl:Class.terms:description: Guilt is the emotion borne from feeling responsible for the commission of an offense and arises out of public humiliation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: guilt

owl:Class.terms:description: grief is an emotion in response to loss, whether physical or abstract including death, unemployment, ill health or the end of a relationship.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: grief

owl:Class.terms:description: hope is an emotion of belief in a positive outcome related to events and circumstances in one's life.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hope

owl:Class.terms:description: Hostility is the intense negative emotion of being in conflict or opposition to someone or something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hostility

owl:Class.terms:description: hurt is an unpleasant feeling, emotion or sensation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hurt

owl:Class.terms:description: Hysteria is an unmanageable emotion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hysteria

owl:Class.terms:description: indifference is an emotion characterized by lack of interest, concern, or sympathy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: indifference

owl:Class.terms:description: interest is the emotion of wanting to know or learn about something or someone.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: interest

owl:Class.terms:description: jealousy is an emotion and typically refers to the negative thoughts and feelings of insecurity, fear, and anxiety over an anticipated loss of something that the person values, particularly in reference to a human connection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: jealousy

owl:Class.terms:description: joy is an emotion of intense happiness.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: joy

owl:Class.terms:description: loathing is an intense dislike or disgust.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: loathing

owl:Class.terms:description: Loneliness is an unpleasant emotion in which a person feels a strong sense of emptiness, yearning distress and solitude resulting from inadequate quantity or quality of social relationships.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: loneliness

owl:Class.terms:description: lust is the strong desire for sex.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: lust

owl:Class.terms:description: misery is a feeling of great unhappiness, suffering and/or pain.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: misery

owl:Class.terms:description: Panic is a sudden emotion of fear which is so strong as to dominate or prevent reason and logical thinking, replacing it with overwhelming feelings of anxiety and frantic agitation consistent with an animalistic fight-or-flight reaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: panic

owl:Class.terms:description: passion is the intense desire for something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: passion

owl:Class.terms:description: Pity is the emotion of sadness or sorrow for another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pity

owl:Class.terms:description: pleasure is an emotion of happy satisfaction and enjoyment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pleasure

owl:Class.terms:description: pride is an emotion of satisfaction of attachment toward one's own or another's choices and actions, or toward a whole group of people, and is a product of praise, independent self-reflection, or a fulfilled feeling of belonging.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pride

owl:Class.terms:description: Rage is a feeling of intense anger that is associated with the Fight-or-flight response.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: rage

owl:Class.terms:description: regret is a feeling of sadness, repentance, or disappointment over something that has happened or been done.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regret

owl:Class.terms:description: remorse is an emotion of personal regret felt by a person after he or she has committed an act which they deem to be shameful, hurtful, or violent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: remorse

owl:Class.terms:description: sadness is emotional pain associated with, or characterized by feelings of disadvantage, loss, despair, helplessness, sorrow, and rage.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sadness

owl:Class.terms:description: satisfaction is an emotion of fulfillment of one's wishes, expectations, or needs, or the pleasure derived from this.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: satisfaction

owl:Class.terms:description: shame is the emotion borne from feeling responsible for the commission of an offense.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shame

owl:Class.terms:description: shock is an emotion of sudden upset or surprise.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shock

owl:Class.terms:description: shyness is an emotion of apprehension, lack of comfort, or awkwardness experienced when in proximity to, approaching, or being approached by other individuals, especially in new situations or with unfamiliar individuals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shyness

owl:Class.terms:description: sorrow is the emotion that is characterized by a long term state of intense sadness, distress and a degree of resignation (not accepting).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sorrow

owl:Class.terms:description: Suffering is the unpleasant emotion and aversion associated with the perception of harm or threat of harm in an individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: suffering

owl:Class.terms:description: surprise is a brief emotion experienced as the result of an unexpected event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: surprise

owl:Class.terms:description: terror is the extreme feeling of fear.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: terror

owl:Class.terms:description: wonder is an emotion of perceiving something very rare or unexpected, but not threatening.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: wonder

owl:Class.terms:description: worry is the emotion characterized by concer over a real or imaginary issue.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: worry

owl:Class.terms:description: modifying is the process by which an entity gains or loses parts, qualities, roles, dispositions, functions, etc, but maintains their identity through these changes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: modifying

owl:Class.terms:description: reproducing is a process characterized by creation of an entity that is similar or exactly the same as the template from which it is derived.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reproducing

owl:Class.terms:description: conversing a form of interactive, spontaneous communication between two or more agents who are following rules of etiquette.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: conversing

owl:Class.terms:description: apprehension is the negative emotion that something unpleasant will occur.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apprehension

owl:Class.terms:description: resentment is disgust directed toward a higher status individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: resentment

owl:Class.terms:description: Pain is an unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pain

owl:Class.terms:description: communicating is the process of conveying information through the exchange of thoughts, messages, or information, as by speech, visuals, signals, writing, or behaviour.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: communicating

owl:Class.terms:description: observational study draws inferences about the possible effect of a treatment on subjects, where the assignment of subjects into a treated group versus a control group is outside the control of the investigator
owl:Class.rdfs:label: observational study

owl:Class.terms:description: An experiment is an investigation that has the goal of verifying, falsifying, or establishing the validity of a hypothesis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: experiment

owl:Class.terms:description: literature curation is the process of an agent selecting and extracting terms and phrases from a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: literature curation

owl:Class.terms:description: A procedure is a process that attempts to achieve one or more objectives by following an established set of actions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: procedure

owl:Class.terms:description: A clinical trial is an intervention trial to determine the safety and efficacy of medical interventions (e.g., drugs, diagnostics, devices, therapy protocols).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical trial

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical diagnosis (often simply termed diagnosis) refers to the process of attempting to determine or identify a possible disease or disorder.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical diagnosis

owl:Class.terms:description: A differential diagnosis (sometimes abbreviated DDx, ddx, DD, D/Dx, or ) is a systematic diagnostic method used to identify the presence of an entity where multiple alternatives are possible (and the process may be termed differential diagnostic procedure), and may also refer to any of the included candidate alternatives (which may also be termed candidate condition).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: differential diagnosis

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical effect is a chemical interaction in which a chemical elicits a marked characteristic of a biological system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical effect

owl:Class.terms:description: A drug-drug interaction is an interaction in which two drugs interact in such a way to produce a non-additive biological response.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: drug drug interaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An assay is an investigative (analytic) procedure in laboratory medicine, pharmacology, environmental biology, and molecular biology for qualitatively assessing or quantitatively measuring the presence or amount or the functional activity of a target entity (the analyte) which can be a drug or biochemical substance or a cell in an organism or organic sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: assay

owl:Class.terms:description: A diagnostic test is a procedure performed to confirm, or determine the presence of disease in an individual suspected of having the disease, usually following the report of symptoms, or based on the results of other medical tests.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnostic test

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical screening is a medical test or series used to detect or predict the presence of disease in individuals at risk for disease within a defined group, such as a population, family, or workforce
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical screening

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical procedure is a procedure to identify, examine, alleviate or eliminate an undesirable biological disease or disorder.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical procedure

owl:Class.terms:description: An intervention study has the objective of improving the condition of an individual or a group of individuals, and demonstrates the magnitude of that capability by comparing it to a control group.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: intervention study

owl:Class.terms:description: sampling is the act of obtaining a sample, whether through selection, collection or preparation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sampling

owl:Class.terms:description: data analysis is a process of inspecting, cleaning, transforming, and modeling data with the goal of highlighting useful information, suggesting conclusions, and supporting decision making.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: data analysis

owl:Class.terms:description: data collection is the process of acquiring information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: data collection

owl:Class.terms:description: measuring is the process of determining the size, amount, or degree of (something) by using an instrument or device marked in standard units
owl:Class.rdfs:label: measuring

owl:Class.terms:description: observing is a process of passive interaction in which one entity makes note of attributes of one or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: observing

owl:Class.terms:description: gesturing is a form of non-verbal communication in which visible bodily actions communicate particular messages, either in place of speech or together and in parallel with spoken words. Gestures include movement of the hands, face, or other parts of the body.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gesturing

owl:Class.terms:description: A study is a process that realizes the steps of a study design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study

owl:Class.terms:description: In a controlled observational cohort study, two groups of subjects are selected from two populations that are thought to differ in only one characteristic. The groups of subjects are studied for a specific period and contrasted at the end of the study period.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: controlled observational cohort study

owl:Class.terms:description: A microarray experiment is an experiment that involves a microarray device to measure the expression of one or more genes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: microarray experiment

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of transcription

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of translation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the creation or destruction of a molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of molecular quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the production of a molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of molecular production

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the destruction of a molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of molecular degradation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process mediated by a protein that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: protein mediated regulation of translation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process mediated by rna that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: rna mediated regulation of translation

owl:Class.terms:description: The process of maintaining some the frequency, rate or extent of another process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: process maintenance

owl:Class.terms:description: The increase of regulation leads to a increased occurence of processes of the target type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased frequency of process from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: The increase of regulation leads to a decreased occurence of processes of the target process type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased frequency of process from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a process duration is a process that modulates the frequency of another process relative to some reference process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of process frequency

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a process duration is a process that modulates the duration of another process relative to some reference process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of process duration

owl:Class.terms:description: increased duration of process from increased regulation is a process in which the duration of the target process is increased as a result of increased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased duration of process from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: decreased duration of process from increased regulation is a process in which the duration of the target process is decreased as a result of increased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased duration of process from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a process spatial extent is a process that modulates the spatial extent of another process relative to some reference process.
owl:Class.resource:example: heating the solution causes greater diffusion of a chemical.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of process spatial extent

owl:Class.terms:description: The increase of regulation leads to a increased spatial extent of the target process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased spatial extent of process from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: The increase of regulation leads to a decreased spatial extent of the target process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased spatial extent of process from decreased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: maintenance of spatial extent of process is a regulation of a process' spatial extent within some specified parameter.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: maintenance of spatial extent of process

owl:Class.terms:description: maintenance of duration of process is a process that regulates a target process to maintain its duration within an expected interval.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: maintenance of duration of process

owl:Class.terms:description: maintenance of frequency of process is a process that regulates the number of occurences of a target process type to a specified number or interval.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: maintenance of frequency of process

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a participant quantity is the regulation of a process in which the quantity of its partcipants is changed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of object quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: increased regulation leads to an increase in the number of target objects of a specified type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased object production from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: increased regulation leads to a decrease in the number of target objects of a specified type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased object production from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: increased regulation leads to an increase in the consumption of an object of specified type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased object consumption from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: increased regulation leads to an decrease in the consumption of an object of specified type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased object consumption from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the consumption of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of object consumption

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a participant quantity is the regulation of a process in which the quantity of a selected participant is increased.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of object production

owl:Class.terms:description: maintenance of quantity of object production is a regulation of object production in which the number of objects produced is held more or less constant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: maintenance of quantity of object production

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of a participant quantity is the regulation of a process in which the quantity of a selected participant is maintained at a steady level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: maintenance of level of object consumption

owl:Class.terms:description: A mass spectrometry experiment is an experiment that involves the use of a mass spectrometer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mass spectrometry experiment

owl:Class.terms:description: A web service invocation involves the execution of a web service.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: web service invocation

owl:Class.terms:description: A SADI web service invocation is the excution of a SADI web service.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SADI web service invocation

owl:Class.terms:description: Behaviour is the set of actions and mannerisms made by systems (biological or otherwise) in response to stimuli or inputs, whether internal or external, conscious or subconscious, overt or covert, and voluntary or involuntary.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: behaviour

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the destruction of a molecule as a result of increased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased molecular degradation from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the destruction of a molecule as a result of decreased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased molecular degradation from decreased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the destruction of a molecule as a result of decreased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased molecular degradation from decreased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the destruction of a molecule as a result of increased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased molecular degradation from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the production of a molecule as a result of increased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased molecular production from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the production of a molecule as a result of increased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased molecular production from increased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the production of a molecule as a result of decreased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased molecular production from decreased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: A process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the production of a molecule as a result of decreased regulation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased molecular production from decreased regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: increased chemical destruction is a process in which there is an increase in the amount of chemical destroyed relative to some reference process
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased chemical destruction

owl:Class.terms:description: decreased chemical destruction is a process in which there is a decrease in the amount of chemical destroyed relative to some reference process
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased chemical destruction

owl:Class.terms:description: Humiliation is the abasement of pride, which creates mortification or leads to a state of being humbled or reduced to lowliness or submission.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: humiliation

owl:Class.terms:description: hunger is the craving for food.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hunger

owl:Class.terms:description: Discouragement is the emtion of having lost confidence or enthusiasm.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: discouragement

owl:Class.terms:description: satisfaction is the emotion of fulfillling one's wishes, expectations, or needs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: satisfaction

owl:Class.terms:description: suicidal is the emotion of being deeply unhappy or depressed with thoughts of killing one's self.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: suicidal

owl:Class.terms:description: irritability is the negative emotion of quick excitability to annoyance, impatience, or anger.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: irritability

owl:Class.terms:description: indecision is the emotion of being unable to choose between two or more possible courses of action.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: indecision

owl:Class.terms:description: speech is the expression of thoughts and feelings by sound.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: speech

owl:Class.terms:description: the regulation or maintenance of information
owl:Class.rdfs:label: information maintenance

owl:Class.dc:description: a medical intervention is a medical procedure to treat (to cure or alleviate) a health condition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical intervention

owl:Class.dc:description: chemical exposure is a process to expose one or more individuals to a chemical substance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical exposure

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical interaction is a biochemical process in which chemical entities interact through some set of attractive forces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical interaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A biochemical reaction is a biochemical process that involves the conversion of at least one chemical participant (target) into another (product) by an enzyme (agent).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: chemical transport is the directed movement of a chemical entity by some agent (e.g. transporter).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical transport

owl:Class.terms:description: active transport is the movement of a substance across a membrane against its concentration gradient (from low to high concentration) and requires chemical energy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: molecular complex formation is the process of forming a molecular complex from its constituent parts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular complex formation

owl:Class.terms:description: molecular complex disassociation is the process of dissambly of a molecular complex into its constitutent parts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular complex dissociation

owl:Class.terms:description: regulation of biochemical process is a process that changes the frequency, rate or extent of a target biochemical process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulation of biochemical process

owl:Class.terms:description: biochemical activation is a molecular interaction that increases the catalytic rate of the target enzyme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical activation

owl:Class.terms:description: biochemical inhibition is a molecular interaction that decreases the catalytic rate of the target enzyme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical inhibition

owl:Class.terms:description: process up-regulation is a process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of one or more processes in relation to a reference state.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: process up-regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: process down-regulation is a process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of one or more processes in relation to a reference state.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: process down-regulation

owl:Class.terms:description: transcription is the process of creating a complementary RNA copy of a sequence of DNA.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: transcription

owl:Class.terms:description: translation is the process of producing a polypeptide from a ribonucleic acid by a ribosome.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: translation

owl:Class.terms:description: Molecular modification is chemical alteration of a known and previously characterized lead compound for the purpose of enhancing its usefulness as a drug. This could mean enhancing its specificity for a particular body target site, increasing its potency, improving its rate and extent of absorption, modifying to advantage its time course in the body, reducing its toxicity, changing its physical or chemical properties (like solubility) to provide desired features.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular modification

owl:Class.terms:description: Metabolism is the set of chemical processes that occur within a living organism in order to maintain life.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: metabolism

owl:Class.terms:description: Anabolism is the set of metabolic processes that take apart larger chemical entities units into smaller chemical entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: catabolism

owl:Class.terms:description: Anabolism is the set of metabolic processes that construct larger chemical entities units from smaller chemical entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anabolism

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical reaction is a process that leads to the transformation of one set of chemical substances to another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An acid-base reaction is a chemical reaction between an acid and a base.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: acid-base reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A catalyzed reaction is a chemical reaction that is facilitated by a catalyst.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: catalyzed reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A redox reaction is a chemical reaction in which there is a net movement of electrons from one reactant to another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: redox reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An inorganic reaction is a chemical reaction that involves the transformation of inorganic molecules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: inorganic reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A decomposition reaction is an inorganic reaction in which molecule is fragmented into submolecules or atoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decomposition reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A displacement reaction is an inorganic reaction in which a elementary substance displaces and sets free a constituent atom from a molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: displacement reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A double displacement reaction is a displacement reaction in which two molecules swap ions, effectively displacing each other to form two new molecules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: double displacement reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A single displacement reaction where one atom is transferred out of one molecule and into another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: single displacement reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A synthesis reaction is an inorganic reaction in which two or more molecules are chemically bonded together to produce a single product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: synthesis reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An organic reaction is a chemical reaction involving at least one organic molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An isomerization reaction is a chemical reaction in which a molecule is converted into its isomer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: isomerization reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An addition reaction is an organic reaction where two or more molecules combine to form a larger one. Addition reactions are limited to chemical compounds that have multiply-bonded atoms: * Molecules with carbon-carbon double bonds or triple bonds * Molecules with carbon - hetero double bonds like C=O or C=N
owl:Class.rdfs:label: addition reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A polar addition reaction is an addition reaction involving polar residues.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polar addition reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A non-polar addition reaction is an addition reaction involving non-polar residues.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: non-polar addition reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A free radical addition is a non-polar addition reaction involving free radicals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: free radical addition

owl:Class.terms:description: A nucleophilic addition reaction is an addition reaction where a pi bond is removed by the creation of two new covalent bonds by the addition from a nucleophile.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleophilic addition reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An electrophilic addition reaction is a polar addition reaction where a pi bond is removed by the creation of two new covalent bonds.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: electrophilic addition reaction
